{"word":"H3864 - לוּבִי - Lûwbîy - loo-bee' - Lubim","slug":"H3864","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">לוּבִי</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Lûwbîy"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>loo-bee'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Lubim"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DC;&#x05D1;&#x05BC;&#x05D9;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05DC;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05D1;&#x05D9; - lu&#x0302;b&#x0131;&#x0302;y  lu&#x0302;bb&#x0131;&#x0302;y</b> - <i>loo-bee', loob-bee'</i><p/>Patrial from a name probably derived from an unused root meaning to <i>thirst</i>, that is, a <i>dry</i> region; apparently a <i>Libyan</i> or inhabitant of interior Africa (only in plural): - Lubim (-s), Libyans."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3863\">H3863</a>, <a href=\"#/H3865\">H3865</a>, <a href=\"#/H3866\">H3866</a>, <a href=\"#/H3884\">H3884</a>"}]}